<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 120 
                    The Assistant to the Secretary of State (
                        Bohlen
                    ) to the Ambassador in the Soviet Union
                        (
                        Harriman
                    )Sent over the signature of Byrnes.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d120</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">120</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-04T14:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-04T14:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-04T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-04T14:00:00-05:00" n="120" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>/6–2745:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 120 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant to the Secretary of State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BCE2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bohlen</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_HWA2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d120fn1">Sent over the signature of <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-04T15:00:00-04:00">July 4, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1513. Top secret and personal for the Ambassador from <persName corresp="#p_BCE2">Bohlen</persName>.</p>
                <p>I confirmed with the Secretary that both the President and he desire you to be
                    present at Berlin. You should also bring <persName corresp="#p_PEJ1">Page</persName>. Your 2297, June 27.<note n="2" xml:id="d120fn2">
                        <ref target="#d106">Document No. 106</ref>.</note> We think it would be a
                    good idea for you to go to Berlin a day or two in advance in order to look over
                    accommodations and arrangements for civilian personnel. Official instructions
                    follow.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
